Capital League 1

Placings 1983 to 2019 (37 seasons)

 

This league is at Tier 2 in the Brisbane football system and has been directly below the Brisbane Premier League since 1983.

 

This league has been known as:

  • Division 1 (1983)
  • Intermediate League (1984-1986)
  • Division 2 (1987-1996)
  • Semi Pro Division [North and South divisions] (1997 to 2000)
  • Semi Pro Division [single division] (2001)
  • Division 1 (2002)
  • Premier Division 1 (2003-2012)
  • Capital League 1 (since 2013)

 

The placings below in two tables are based on Brisbane Tier 2 standings at the end of the regular season, prior to the final series:

1. Season by season 1983 to 2002

2. Season by season 2003 to 2019

3. Ranking of clubs
